  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: On same device there are 2 accounts:\r\n1. new account with non-default status/username\r\n2. recovered account with default username and empty status\r\nIf status for account 1 was modified and than user opens Edit profile for account 2 then it contains status from account 1. \r\n\r\n![screenshot_20170821-160746](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/29523770-5ccb1092-868e-11e7-9eb0-323f2c5762b2.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nFor recovered account by default there is no status on all screens\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nIf status for account 1 was modified and than user opens Edit profile for recovered account 2 then it contains status from account 1. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nhttps://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/6400348/sessions/6/?accessToken=ynIlyFzd7IFCuwm68nxy4zK1-VQ\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create new account 1\r\n- Open profile for account 1\r\n- Tap on 3 dots to get to Edit Profile screen (it's important to modify status/username on Edit profile screen, not in the drawer)\r\n- On Edit Profile screen change default status to \"Status from first account\" and username to \"First account username\", tap on Save button\r\n- Switch users\r\n- On Sign in screen, tap on Recover account\r\n- Type something in passphrase and some password you'll remember, tap on Recover button to get account recovered\r\n- Sign in into recovered account\r\n- Open Drawer - empty status is shown\r\n- Tap on 3 dots (top right corner) - empty status is shown\r\n- Tap on 3 dots to open Edit profile screen and check content of the Status field.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: released 0.9.10 and develop build for next 0.9.11:  0.9.10-22-g92f3f9a4+\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.3.3\r\n\r\n",
